Portuguese investor Miguel Pais do
Amaral will make a proposal to buy Banco Efisa, the investment
banking unit of Banco Portugues de Negocios SA, Diario Economico
reported, citing Pais do Amaral.  Pais do Amaral will bid through holding company Partrouge,
the Portuguese newspaper said. Banco Portugues de Negocios was
seized by the  Portuguese government  in 2008.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
